  "footnotes": [
    "T (Tripolitania): western coastal Libya, centered on Tripoli; site of Phoenician Oea, Sabratha, and Leptis Magna; under the Karamanli dynasty (1711–1835) as a semi-autonomous Ottoman vassal; seat of the Government of National Unity (GNU) since 2015",
    "C (Cyrenaica): eastern Libya centered on Benghazi; the Pentapolis was founded c.631 BCE by Greek colonists from Thera; passed to Ptolemaic Egypt, then Rome (96 BCE), then Byzantine; home to the rival HoR / LNA government since 2014",
    "F (Fezzan): vast interior/southwestern desert; the Garamantian Kingdom controlled trans-Saharan trade routes for over a millennium; the Awlad Muhammad dynasty (1577–1842) ruled as an Ottoman vassal; administered by France (1943–1951) after WWII",
    "Banu Hilal / Banu Sulaym (1048): Arab tribal confederations sent by the Fatimid caliph al-Mustansir to punish the Zirid ruler; their migration transformed the demography of the Maghreb and devastated urban agricultural society",
    "Karamanli dynasty (1711–1835): founded by Yusuf Karamanli who seized power from the Ottoman governor; the dynasty fought the First Barbary War with the United States (1801–05) over tribute; the Ottomans reasserted direct rule in 1835",
    "Post-2011 split: the Government of National Unity (GNU) controls Tripolitania and is backed by Turkey and the UN; the House of Representatives (HoR) and Libyan National Army (LNA) under Khalifa Haftar control Cyrenaica and parts of Fezzan, backed by the UAE and Russia"
  ]
